BLOCK B — Authorization & Request Protection

Objective: Learn how authenticated users abuse permissions and how modern web applications prevent it.


---

1. Authentication vs Authorization

This is one of the most common interview questions.

Authentication	Authorization

Who are you?	What can you do?
Identity verification	Permission verification
Login	Access control
Username + Password, MFA	Roles, Policies, Permissions


Example

You log into Barclays.

Authentication:

Username

Password

MFA


System verifies:

> "Yes, this is Suresh."



Now Authorization starts.

System checks:

Can Suresh access Payroll?

Can Suresh access HR Portal?

Can Suresh access Admin APIs?



---

Real Barclays Example

Employee logs in.

Authentication: ✔ Identity verified.

Authorization decides:

Developer:

GitHub ✔

Jenkins ✔

Production Database ❌


Security Consultant:

SIEM ✔

Incident Response ✔

Payroll ❌



---

Manager's WHY

Why separate Authentication and Authorization?

Because verifying identity doesn't mean giving all permissions.

Otherwise every logged-in employee becomes an administrator.


